# Pokemon Web — Cursor Rules

> See `AGENTS.md` for full project context, dependency graph, key interfaces,
> file-finding shortcuts, common task recipes, and anti-patterns.

## Project

Browser-based Pokémon RPG: Phaser 3 + TypeScript 6.x + Vite 8.x. Client-side only.

## Key Commands

- `npm run dev` — Dev server
- `npm run build` — Type-check + build (run before committing)
- `npm run test` — Unit + integration tests (< 2s)
- `npm run test:e2e` — Playwright E2E tests

## Import Convention

Use path aliases and barrel imports:
```typescript
import { BattleManager } from '@battle';       // NOT from '@battle/core/BattleManager'
import { GameManager } from '@managers';
import { pokemonData } from '@data/pokemon';
```

Aliases: `@scenes/*`, `@entities/*`, `@data/*`, `@managers/*`, `@systems/*`, `@ui/*`, `@utils/*`, `@config/*`, `@battle/*`

## Code Style

- `const` over `let`; never `var`
- TypeScript interfaces for all data structures (see `frontend/src/data/interfaces.ts`)
- One Phaser Scene per file
- Data files = pure data, no logic
- Scenes communicate via `EventManager`, never direct references
- All game state through `GameManager`

## File Placement

| Type | Location |
|---|---|
| Scenes | `frontend/src/scenes/<domain>/` |
| Entities | `frontend/src/entities/` |
| Battle logic | `frontend/src/battle/` |
| Pure data | `frontend/src/data/` |
| Managers | `frontend/src/managers/` |
| Systems | `frontend/src/systems/` |
| UI | `frontend/src/ui/` |
| Utils | `frontend/src/utils/` |
| Tests | `tests/unit/`, `tests/integration/`, `tests/e2e/` |

## Context Files

Each `frontend/src/` directory has a `CONTEXT.md` with navigational information.
Read these before exploring a directory.

## Anti-Patterns

- Don't import from files directly — use barrel `index.ts` exports
- Don't reference scenes directly — use `EventManager`
- Don't put logic in data files
- Don't rewrite map grids from scratch — use the map toolchain
- Don't skip `npm run build` before committing
- Don't use `git add -A` — stage files individually

## After Changes

1. Run `npm run build` (zero errors required)
2. Run `npm run test`
3. Update `docs/CHANGELOG.md`
4. Update affected `CONTEXT.md` if files were added/removed/renamed
5. Update `docs/architecture.md` if structure changed
6. Git: `git add <specific-files>` then commit with imperative mood
